race.comment: TIGER TOWN (6) was ridden closer to the pace and battled on bravely to be beaten under a length last start over 1400m at Kembla. Placed two from two when third-up so although coming back to 1300m she should be ready to peak. PROBABILITY THEORY (9) was crunched from 7.0 into 5.0 and duly got the cash last time out in a maiden over this course and distance. Has only raced twice and is progressing nicely. Looks up to this. SMART SERENADE (4) did a good job to finish a close third in open company over this distance at Muswellbrook at his last run a month ago. Perfectly drawn and back in a BM64 looks a serious contender. YABBY PUMP (2) didn't lie down and wasn't beaten far when resuming at Newcastle recently. Won a Class 1 here at this trip last prep. Must be considered. UP TO MISCHIEF (5) has won two from three when fresh so keep her in mind despite an eight-month gap between runs.
